issue.title: ðŸš€ Performance: Add component memoization for optimization
issue.body:
## Summary
- Implements comprehensive React performance optimizations to resolve #47
- Adds useMemo for expensive calculations like game statistics and BPI
- Uses useCallback for stable event handlers and game actions
- Memoizes frequently re-rendering components with React.memo

## Performance Improvements

### ðŸ§® Expensive Calculations Optimized
- **GameStatistics.tsx**: Memoized `calculateStats()` function that processes player statistics
- **PlayerScoreCard.tsx**: Memoized BPI and percentage calculations that run on every render
- **EndGameModal.tsx**: Memoized game duration and highest run calculations

### ðŸ”„ Event Handlers Stabilized  
- **App.tsx**: Memoized theme toggle, fullscreen, sign out, and game state callbacks
- **GameScoring**: Memoized table acceptance and re-break handlers
- **Navigation**: Stable callbacks prevent unnecessary child re-renders

### ðŸŽ¯ Components Memoized
- **PlayerScoreCard**: Prevents re-renders when other players' data changes
- **ScoreButton**: Optimized for stable rendering during scoring
- **MatchTimer**: Prevents unnecessary timer component re-renders
- **EndGameModal**: Optimized modal rendering with expensive calculations

## Technical Details

- All optimizations maintain existing functionality - no breaking changes
- Proper dependency arrays specified for all hooks
- Strategic component memoization on render-heavy components
- Tests pass and build completes successfully

## Performance Impact

- **Reduced cascading re-renders** from App component's 16+ state variables
- **Optimized expensive operations** that previously ran on every render  
- **Stable callback references** prevent unnecessary child component updates
- **Improved user experience** during intensive game state updates

## Test Plan
- [x] All existing tests pass
- [x] Build completes without errors  
- [x] App functionality remains unchanged
- [x] Performance improvements verified through reduced re-render cycles

Closes #47

issue.title: Add Support for Secret Scanning Push Protection Bypasses & Scan History API Endpoints
issue.body:
### Description
There are two Secret Scanning endpoints available in the GitHub REST API which in my opinion aren't present in the go-github

- Creates a bypass for a previously push protected secret.
   `POST /repos/{owner}/{repo}/secret-scanning/push-protection-bypasses`

- Retrieves scan history of a repository.
   `GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/secret-scanning/scan-history`

These endpoints would be helpful for directly checking past secret scanning findings and managing push protection bypasses.

### References:
[https://docs.github.com/en/rest/secret-scanning/secret-scanning?apiVersion=2022-11-28#create-a-push-protection-bypass](https://docs.github.com/en/rest/secret-scanning/secret-scanning?apiVersion=2022-11-28#create-a-push-protection-bypass)
[https://docs.github.com/en/rest/secret-scanning/secret-scanning?apiVersion=2022-11-28#get-secret-scanning-scan-history-for-a-repository](https://docs.github.com/en/rest/secret-scanning/secret-scanning?apiVersion=2022-11-28#get-secret-scanning-scan-history-for-a-repository)

I will be happy to contribute to the implementation of these Secret Scanning endpoints.

> Set up secure Firebase initialization using environment variables in the repository.

> - Create a .env.example file containing the required Firebase config keys (do not include secrets).

> - Add instructions as a comment in .env.example.
> - Verify no secrets are committed.
>

issue.title: Create golden test infrastructure

milestone.title: L1 - Contracts & Preview
milestone.description: Offline operation: PromptSpec & ProviderSpec schemas, loader/validator, translation preview, real lossiness reporting

issue.body:
## ðŸ“‹ Task Overview
Establish golden test infrastructure with snapshot testing setup, corpus management, and comparison logic for validating translation outputs and lossiness reports.

## ðŸŽ¯ Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Set up snapshot testing framework
- [ ] Create test corpus structure
- [ ] Implement snapshot comparison
- [ ] Support updating golden files
- [ ] Handle JSON normalization for comparison
- [ ] Generate diff reports for failures
- [ ] Support provider-specific snapshots
- [ ] Version golden files with schema versions

## ðŸ“Š Technical Details
### Implementation Approach
Golden test system:
1. Organize test corpus
2. Capture translation outputs
3. Compare against golden files

### Dependencies
- Tests: All translation components
- Uses: #9 (translate() function)

### Test Structure
```
tests/golden/
  prompts/
    basic.json
    complex_tools.json
  snapshots/
    openai/
      basic.golden.json
    anthropic/
      basic.golden.json
```

## âš ï¸ Risks & Considerations
- Golden file maintenance
- Version compatibility
- Cross-platform differences
- Large snapshot sizes

## ðŸ§ª Testing Requirements
- Unit: Comparison logic
- Integration: Snapshot workflow
- Meta: Test the test framework
- Performance: Large corpus handling

## ðŸ“š Documentation Requirements
- [ ] Document test structure
- [ ] Explain golden updates
- [ ] Provide test authoring guide

## ðŸ”— References
- Epic: #5 (Testing Framework)
- Critical for: Quality assurance

## â±ï¸ Estimates
- **Effort**: M
- **Time**: 4-5 hours
- **Complexity**: Medium

comment.body:
Completed implementation of golden test infrastructure! ðŸŽ‰

The infrastructure includes:
- **specado-golden crate**: Complete snapshot testing framework
- **SnapshotManager**: Reading/writing/updating snapshots with backup support
- **DiffEngine**: Smart JSON comparison with normalization and volatile field handling
- **CorpusManager**: Test discovery and organization across categories
- **GoldenTestRunner**: Test execution with parallel support and detailed reporting
- **Test Macros**: `golden_test!` and `golden_test_batch!` for ergonomic testing
- **Initial Corpus**: 5 test cases across basic, complex, edge-cases, and provider categories

Key features:
- Snapshot updates via `UPDATE_GOLDEN=1` environment variable
- Intelligent JSON diffing with float tolerance
- Field ignoring for timestamps and volatile data
- Test categorization and tagging system
- CI-friendly operation with clear error messages
- Comprehensive documentation in golden-corpus/README.md

The infrastructure is ready for use and can be expanded with additional test cases as needed.
